
  <sn><md>### Weathering of Feldspathoid Family

**Feldspathoids** are important minerals that are `closely related to feldspars` but are `lower in` $\mathrm{SiO_2}$ content. The most common members of this family are `Leucite` and `Nepheline`.</md></sn>
